AGI - The core of Europe is set in the rocky wall of Monte Taleo. The roots of the European Union are clinging to the sanctuary of the Holy Ghost of Subiaco> well distant from the island of Ventotene where the Manifesto was written at the center of the political bagarre of these hours: it is the 'rule' that characterizes the days of the European Conservatives arrived today in the small Lazio village, at the gates of Rome, to celebrate Saint Benedict>, patron of Europe, and dedicated to the European "Christian roots". A 'rule' declined to the present by the European Conservators in the places where a very young San Benedetto da Norcia> forged its "pray and work".
<h2> Participation of MEPs ECR</h2>
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
On the three black minivans directed to the monastery built around the cave where the Christian monk lived as an hermit, travel about thirty Europeans of the Ecr. A wide range of European Conservatives of different nationalities: Italian, Spanish, Finnish, Cypriot, and French. They come from Brussels where today Giorgia Meloni> has claimed, after the European Council, the results obtained from Italy. And the mission overlaps the day still 'hot' with the opposition to the Premier attack after the words on Ventotene.
<h2> European Conservatives' message
Defending its roots, a Confederal Europe based on the principle of subsidiarity without erasing the powers of individual States: is the mantra of the initiative that makes the bis after that last year, always in Subiaco, the "Carta dei valori conservatori" was signed.
<h2> Visit to the Holy Ghost and testimonies</h2>
The greedy eyes of foreign MEPs 'photograph' the unprecedented pause from the political agon during the visit to the monastery after the Mass at the Sacred Spec of Subiaco>. A caresss to the statue of San Benedetto>, a look at the breathtaking panorama from the rocky hill in the upper Aniene Valley, the inevitable selfies. Then the journey back to the country between the hairpin bends, illuminated by the torch at the edge of the road and the off-plan of a mother who chases through the woods the young boy scout (in night trip) to bring him the jacket.
<h2> The words of Procaccini on the role of San Benedetto</h2>
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
The sense of the initiative is summed up by the words of the Conservatives' co-president in the European Parliament, Nicola Procaccini>. "In these years we have tried to place the Ventotene Manifesto in the heart of the construction of Europe as if it were a kind of sacred text. This - says to AGI the Euro MP of Brothers of Italy - is a historical forcing because it was a respectable text but of part that has nothing to do with Europe that was then planned that it was a confederal and not federalist Europe. This is the right opportunity to say that Europe is the daughter of Saint Benedict, of the patron of Europe and is certainly not the daughter of Spinelli or of others, respectable characters of our history also heroic, courageous but from an ideal point of view the core of European identity is here in Subiaco is not in Ventotene".
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
For Procaccini> "any idea of spirituality within the European Union has been banned despite St Benedict's not only a religious figure but a key figure for the very existence of a European culture on which political identity is formed. It is therefore necessary to bring back a key figure of history, beyond the religious aspect, in the heart of European construction."
<h2> The conference programme and celebrations
The event at Subiaco dei Conservatori europea will continue in the morning of tomorrow with the conference scheduled at the Teatro Narzio: the interventions of ministers Alessandro Giuli> and Francesco Lollobrigida>. He will follow the lectio magistralis of Ryszard Legutko>, already co-president of the group Ecr and the greeting of the abbot of Subiaco. Then will speak Nicola Procaccini>, the head delegation of Brothers of Italy to the European Parliament Carlo Fidanza> and the vice-president of Parliament, Antonella Sberna>. Tomorrow afternoon the ECR MEPs, both Italian and from various European nations, will participate in the solemn celebrations for San Benedetto> patron of Europe, with the ignition of the traditional "Fiaccola pro pace et Europa uno". Also anticipated an institutional moment organized by the Municipality of Subiaco, with the video greeting message of the President of the European Parliament, Roberta Metsola>.
